---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { SITES } from "../lib/sites";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
const url = (p: string) => `${base}${p}`;
---

<Layout title="Our Story | Scott's Hospitality">
  <section class="bg-ink pt-32 pb-12 sm:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-gold-light uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-xs mb-4">Our Story</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-cream mb-5 leading-tight">
        Fifty years of opening<br/>
        <span class="italic text-gold-light">new doors.</span>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-cream-soft py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 space-y-8 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-snug italic">
        The original California Scott's Seafood Grill & Bar was established in
        San Francisco in October of 1976 by Malcolm Stroud, Martin Newman, and
        Lloyd Wiborg.
      </p>

      <p>
        Malcolm and Martin were owner-operators of "The Coachman," and Lloyd had
        been a partner in "The Coalyard" — both San Francisco restaurants. Malcolm
        and Martin purchased the building at the corner of Scott and Lombard,
        originally intending to update it and sell it. After consideration, they
        decided to open a seafood restaurant instead. A friend of Malcolm's
        suggested they contact Lloyd as a potential investor and co-owner.
      </p>

      <p>
        They opened to remarkable success, often seating over 500 diners a day with
        only 62 seats. In 1977, <em>Nation's Restaurant News</em> named them the
        <strong class="text-ink">"highest grossing per seat restaurant in the nation."</strong>
      </p>

      <p>
        Through various expansions and licensing deals, there have been ten Scott's
        in California and one in Hawaii. The San Jose restaurant opened in 1985
        and has been a valued part of the downtown community since.
      </p>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-gold pl-6 my-12">
        <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink/90 italic leading-relaxed">
          Steve Mayer joined the Scott's family in the early 2000s. Having served
          as Malcolm's long-term accountant, he helped launch Scott's Palo Alto
          and run Scott's San Jose.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        After Malcolm passed, Steve brought in Sammy Reyes as his partner. When
        Scott's San Jose was bought out of its lease on Park Avenue, Mayor Sam
        Liccardo reached out to Steve to work with his team to find a new home
        for the restaurant. That new home is the current location on 1st Street,
        which Scott's San Jose moved to in 2020. Through a lot of sacrifice and
        hard work, Scott's San Jose stayed open throughout COVID as a place the
        downtown community could enjoy.
      </p>

      <p>
        In 2024, Scott's San Jose entered into a long-term lease with the city's
        Rotary Center to expand offerings into full-service, large-scale events.
        The team hopes to have a full-service bar and rooftop patio there in the
        next year.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl font-display italic text-ink leading-relaxed pt-6">
        Scott's has built a history on finding new doors to open whenever others
        close. Through numerous moves, redecorations, and new concepts, the heart
        of Scott's has always been the dedicated team.
      </p>

      <p>
        Scott's thanks you for your business over the years and looks forward to
        continuing to serve you in the future — for your dining, catering, and
        event planning needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-paper py-20 sm:py-28 border-y border-line">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p class="text-gold-deep uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-xs mb-4">Today</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-5xl text-ink leading-tight">Four concepts. One family.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <a href={`${SITES.restaurant}/`} class="block bg-cream-soft p-6 border-t-2 border-gold hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <p class="text-gold-deep uppercase tracking-widest text-xs mb-2">1985</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Scott's Seafood San Jose</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">The flagship restaurant — on 1st Street since 2020.</p>
        </a>
        <a href={`${SITES.ballroom}/`} class="block bg-cream-soft p-6 border-t-2 border-gold hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <p class="text-gold-deep uppercase tracking-widest text-xs mb-2">2024</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Scott's Ballroom</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Event venue at the San Jose Rotary Summit Center.</p>
        </a>
        <a href={`${SITES.socialClub}/`} class="block bg-cream-soft p-6 border-t-2 border-gold hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <p class="text-gold-deep uppercase tracking-widest text-xs mb-2">2025</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Scott's Social Club</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">A private members' community.</p>
        </a>
        <a href={`${SITES.provisions}/`} class="block bg-cream-soft p-6 border-t-2 border-gold hover:shadow-lg transition">
          <p class="text-gold-deep uppercase tracking-widest text-xs mb-2">2026</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Scott's Provisions</h3>
          <p class="text-ink/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">Catering for workplaces and events.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
